Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: Te Ngakau advised that Sir George Grey should not be received with the usual powhiri or invitation from the women at the entrance to the settlement with the words, "Come here, oh guest," but should welcome him with "Come here, governor, your coming is your own work," meaning they will expect Sir George Grey to state his object in this meeting, and to take the initiative.
